  "text": "(3) f sc (k) is a function for punishment of many-matches, controlling the amount of splitting or merging. 4.2.1.3 MSRA-TD500: Yao et al. [CITATION_1] proposes a new evaluation protocol for rotated bounding box, where both the predicted and ground truth bounding box are revolved horizontal around its center. They are matched only when the standard IOU score is higher than the threshold and the rotation of the original bounding boxes are less a pre-defined value (in practice pi 4 ).",
